description.narrative: El objetivo general del programa es contribuir a la competitividad del sector agrícola en Jamaica a través del logro de los siguientes objetivo s específicos: (i) incrementar la capacidad de pequeños y medianos productores para accesar mercados nacionales e internacionales; (ii) mejorar el desempeño de los sistemas nacilonales de calidad y seguridad de alimentos; y (iii) impulsar el desarrollo de cadenas de valor agropecuarias y de procesamiento de alimentos.

The general objetive of the program is to contribute to the competitiveness of the agricultural sector in Jamaica through the achievement of three specific objectives: (i) increase the capacity of small and medium size famers to access national and international markets; (ii) increase the performance of the country¿s food quality and safety management systems; and (iii) foster the development of agricultural and agro-processing value chains.

activity-description.narrative: A National Animal Health and Welfare Policy is being developed and is expected to guide and support the efforts of government, industry and relevant stakeholders to upgrade the local animal health and welfare systems in order to achieve national and international animal health objectives

Desktops are used alongside other machines to electronically enter data from all departments of the Veterinary Services division to ensure updates from any location. Results from work done can be accessed from anywhere in the office with a two way relationship between the destops and the other equipment. The upgrading of the lab comes in conjunction with the application for ISO 17025 accrediation in January 2014.
More than 33 Public Health and Medical Epidemiological personnel benefited from training in HACCP, Risk Analysis, Epidemiology and Meat Inspection training.

Performance Index of Food Safety, Plant Health and Animal Health Sectors will be measured using IICA/PAHO/PVS methodologies. The performance index for the Food Safety Sector is expected to move from <60% at baseline year to >70% at programme end. For Animal and Plant Health Sectors, indices are expected to move from <60% at baseline year to >80% respectively, at end of ACP.
Specialized raining in Epidemiological Risk Assessment was received by Veterinary Specialist in the Veterinary Services Division of the Ministry of Agriculture & Fisheries

The National Food Safety Policy is the overarching and guiding framework for improving the national food safety program. This Implementation plan is a road map for achieving the policy’s objectives, identifying: activities for each policy objective; clear roles and responsibilities to prevent duplication of efforts; gaps, limitations and interrelated activities; specific timelines, performance indicators and funding requirement; the monitoring and evaluation framework for policy implementation.

The Strategic Action Plan, arising out of stakeholder consultation in December 2012 and based on a consolidated review of the PVS Assessment and the Food Safety Policy Implementation Plan, focuses on practical and achievable actions. It is designed to impact the goals and objectives of the National Food Safety Policy, approved October 2011 and implemented with the participation of all stakeholders, including policy makers, producers, farmers, food business operators, regulators and consumers.
